transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. This is Jimmy. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir. I'm just trying to cancel my account.

Speaker 1: And if possible, I tried to do it through e-mail.

Speaker 2: I think there's an order in progress.

Speaker 1: Is it still able to be canceled at the pharmacy and possibly get a refund?

Speaker 2: I see that it was shipped out basically on the 11th yesterday,

Speaker 1: but all you have to do is just reject that package.

Speaker 2: Just have it returned to sender, and we'll get you credited back for that order.

Speaker 1: But I see that you're getting the Cialis.

Speaker 2: You're getting 30 of them, 20 milligrams.

Speaker 1: Is there any particular reason why you want to cancel?

Speaker 2: You don't mind me asking?

Speaker 1: It's just not too expensive.

Speaker 2: Too expensive? Okay, I understand.

Speaker 1: I can go ahead and take care of that for you.

Speaker 2: Just curious, have you thought about trying our latest and greatest new AGB Viagra?

Speaker 1: Have you heard about that?

Speaker 2: No, thank you.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: It's a lot cheaper and it works a lot better.

Speaker 1: That's why I was asking.

Speaker 2: I understand.

Speaker 1: Okay, I'll go ahead and take care of your request for you.

Speaker 2: Appreciate it.

Speaker 1: When you say return to sender,

Speaker 2: how do I do return to sender when it finally does come within a couple days?

Speaker 1: Yeah, basically the address is on the package,

Speaker 2: but what I will recommend is that you actually take it to the post office

Speaker 1: and you get a tracking number so you know exactly when it comes back.

Speaker 2: And once we receive it, we will credit you the difference on your credit card.

Speaker 1: Okay?

Speaker 2: Okay, I appreciate it.

Speaker 1: All right, not a problem.

Speaker 2: But I went ahead and stopped all your future orders.

Speaker 1: As far as that's concerned, your subscription has been canceled.

Speaker 2: Okay?

Speaker 1: All right, thank you very much.

Speaker 2: All right, have a good one.

Speaker 1: You too.

Speaker 2: All right.
